The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning and artificial intelligence, which are both commonly associated with the cs.AI sub-category. The focus on learning behaviour and constructing temporally extended actions suggests a connection to the cs.LG sub-category. The use of options and intrinsic goals may also relate to the cs.RO and cs.SY sub-categories, which deal with robotics and control systems. Finally, the mention of exploration in environments with sparse rewards may suggest a connection to the cs.CV sub-category, which deals with computer vision and perception in environments.
